Issues.Body:
Goal: in a .netcore 3.1 WPF app, launch an external browser using a WPF Hyperlink NavigationUri property.

```
<Hyperlink NavigateUri="https://www.bing.com/" />
```

Does not work.

Extending the example and using MVVM:

XAML:
```
<Hyperlink 
    CommandParameter="{Binding NavigationUrl}" 
    Command="{Binding RequestNavigateCommand}"
    >ABN</Hyperlink>:
```

C#:
```
private void RequestNavigate(object obj)
        {
            if(obj is string destinationurl)
            {
                ProcessStartInfo sInfo = new ProcessStartInfo("start " + destinationurl);
                /*
                ProcessStartInfo sInfo = new ProcessStartInfo(destinationurl)
                {
                    //UseShellExecute = true,
                    UseShellExecute = false,
                    //Verb = "open"
                    Verb = "start"
                };
                 */
                Process.Start(sInfo);
            }
                //System.Diagnostics.Process.Start("msedge.exe",destinationurl);
                //System.Diagnostics.Process.Start("explorer.exe",destinationurl);
        }
```

